    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "wait, i'm a bit confused. u said allowing exemptions helps maintain the separation of church and state? wouldnt that be the opposite? like, if the gov has to bend its own rules because of religion, isnt that letting religion influence how the state operates? wouldn't that actually weaken the secular nature of the state instead of helping it?",
