      "content": "You're right to question that, but the key difference lies in the context and implementation of exemptions. When exemptions are granted, it's typically to protect the rights of individuals or groups who sincerely hold a particular faith, not to advance a specific religion or ideology. This approach ensures that the government remains neutral and doesn't impose a particular set of beliefs on its citizens.",
      "source": "target",
